Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
specifyIlm(25.10)                                            specifyIlm(25.10)

Name
       specifyIlm - Specifies ILM data directory for the specified block

Syntax
       specifyIlm

       [-help]

       {[-cell <cellName> [-dir <dirName>]] | -cellview <lib cell view>}

       Specifies ILM data directory for the specified block. You can run spec-
       ifyIlm multiple times in the same session. Each time you specify speci-
       fyIlm,  the  software overwrites the previous setting for the block. If
       master/clones exist in the design, the cell name will have the name  of
       the master partition.

       Note:  You  can  use this command only if the ILMs are unflattened (un-
       flattenIlm) or the design is in black box view. You cannot  change  ILM
       settings in flattened or ILM view.

       The  syntax is order-dependent. You must specify -cell before you spec-
       ify -dir.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation for each specifyIlm parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man specifyIlm

       -cell <cellName>
              Specifies the block name.

       -cellview <lib cell view>
              Specifies the library name, cell name, and view name in the Ope-
              nAccess database format.

       -dir <dirName>
              Specifies the directory for the files you want to read.

              Note: This parameter is optional.

              For  OA  flow, the -dir option is not required and specifyIlm is
              used as follows:

              specifyIlm -cell pll_fbdiv

              The flow automatically finds the OA path when the -dir for spec-
              ifyIlm is not set.

Examples
              * The following commands create ilms and specify ilms for an  OA
                design:

                #create ilms for each block

                createInterfaceLogic -cellview {OA_PTN_LIB tdsp_core abstract}

                createInterfaceLogic  -cellview  {OA_PTN_LIB  results_conv ab-
                stract}

                #specify ilms in top level

                specifyIlm -cell tdsp_core

                specifyIlm -cell results_conv

              * The following commands specifies  directory  dir_dsp_core  for
                block tdsp_core, and directory dir_onemore for block onemore:

                specifyIlm -cell tdsp_core -dir dir_dsp_core

                specifyIlm -cell onemore -dir dir_onemore

              * The  following  commands  show  how to reset the ILM directory
                from dir_tdsp_core to dir2_tdsp_core:

                specifyIlm -cell tdsp_core -dir dir_tdsp_core

                specifyIlm -cell tdsp_core -dir dir2_tdsp_core

                These commands are equivalent to the following commands, which
                include unspecifyIlm:

                specifyIlm -cell tdsp_core -dir dir_tdsp_core

                unspecifyIlm -cell tdsp_core

                specifyIlm -cell tdsp_core -dir dir2_tdsp_core

